text:
PROs
Spectacular construction, you’ll be taking pictures every minute;
Luxurious interior, including the carpet that broke the World Record;
Unique and well crafted souvenirs;
A very friendly and knowledgeable guide, we found out a lot of interesting facts from him;
Inside staff very polite and helpful, I was really impressed when someone stopped a small go cart to give us a lift to the end of the long corridor;
Water fountains spread everywhere, you always stay hydrated;
Bathrooms are HUGE and have everything, even spots to cool your feet;
Breathtaking at night!

CONs
Security outside are blunt instruments, expect very sharp and rude answers (might not be their fault, the Mosque conduct might be set that way to ensure safety);
Small isles, we went in September when few people were there but I imagine it gets really crowded;
Women are forced to wear the mosque attire (can’t mess with tradition);
Souvenirs were a bit on the expensive side, but I guess that can be expected.

TIP: Once you pass the security checks and through the corridor, when you arrive at the main entrance, where the arch overlooking the court is look to your right. There will be a panel showing you when the next FREE tour is. Not only will you learn a lot of facts but you can visit areas that are Off limits normally. The guide we had was knowledgeable and had a fun way of relating information and would not accept any other form of appreciation other than our satisfaction. Totally worth the approx. 45 minutes while you are there!
